1 Una medesma lingua pria mi morse, 2 sì che mi tinse l’una e l’altra guancia, 3 e poi la medicina mi riporse;
4 così od’ io che solea far la lancia 5 d’Achille e del suo padre esser cagione 6 prima di trista e poi di buona mancia.

query.result:
**English:**
1 A single tongue had bitten me before, 2 so that it stained both one cheek and the other, 3 and then medicine restored me;
4 thus I heard that the lance of Achilles 5 used to cause, and of his father, 6 first sad and then good fortune.
**Sanskrit:**
1 Ekayā eva jihvayā pūrvam mama daṣṭam, 2 Tena me eka eva gaṇḍaḥ anyaś ca rañjitaḥ, 3 Tataś ca auṣadham mama punar ārogyam ādadau;
4 Evam aham śuśrāva yathā śaktiḥ Akhileśasya 5 Tathā tasya pitur api kāraṇam āsīt 6 Ādi duḥkhasya tataś ca sukhasya.

query.prompt:
Please translate each line literally into English and Sanskrit.
52 E s’ella d’elefanti e di balene 53 non si pente, chi guarda sottilmente, 54 più giusta e più discreta la ne tene;
55 ché dove l’argomento de la mente 56 s’aggiugne al mal volere e a la possa, 57 nessun riparo vi può far la gente.

query.result:
**English:**
52 And if she does not repent of elephants and whales, 53 whoever looks closely, 54 holds her to be more just and more discreet;
55 because where the argument of the mind 56 is added to evil will and power, 57 no defense can people make against it.
**Sanskrit:**
52 Yadyapi sā gajānāṃ tathā timīṅgīlānāṃ 53 na paścāttāpaṃ karoti, yaḥ sūkṣmatayā paśyati, 54 sāṃ nyāyyatarāṃ viśiṣṭatarāṃ ca māṃ manyate;
55 yataḥ yatra manasaḥ prapañcaḥ 56 durbuddhyā saha balena ca yujyate, 57 tatra janāḥ kaścit pratirodhaḥ kartaṃ na śaknuvanti.
